From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MSYS2 packaging <packaging@msys2.org>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] meson: use pthreads on Cygwin

Meson reports MSYS/Cygwin as a Windows host, but the POSIX pthread
interfaces are the native thread API there.  Avoid selecting the Win32
C11 thread implementation and use the ordinary Meson threads dependency.
---
 meson.build               | 2 +-
 src/c11/impl/meson.build  | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -1721,7 +1721,7 @@ elif with_shader_cache
   error('Shader Cache requires compression')
 endif
 
-if host_machine.system() == 'windows'
+if host_machine.system() == 'windows' and cc.get_define('__CYGWIN__') == ''
   # For MSVC and MinGW we aren't using pthreads, and dependency('threads') will add linkage
   # to pthread for MinGW, so leave the dependency null_dep for Windows. For Windows linking to
   # kernel32 is enough for c11/threads.h and it's already linked by meson by default
diff --git a/src/c11/impl/meson.build b/src/c11/impl/meson.build
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/c11/impl/meson.build
+++ b/src/c11/impl/meson.build
@@ -9,7 +9,7 @@ files_mesa_util_c11 = files(
 
 if with_c11_threads
   # no need implement c11 threads
-elif host_machine.system() == 'windows'
+elif host_machine.system() == 'windows' and cc.get_define('__CYGWIN__') == ''
   files_mesa_util_c11 += 'threads_win32.c'
   files_mesa_util_c11 += 'threads_win32_tls_callback.cpp'
 else
-- 
